# deploy/certs/server-ext.cnf — Server certificate SAN extension template
#
# This file is committed to version control with PLACEHOLDER values only.
# The generate-certs.sh script overwrites this file with real values at signing time.
# The overwritten version (with real IP/hostname) is gitignored via deploy/certs/*.cnf — wait,
# actually *.cnf is NOT gitignored — the script writes the real-values version here and
# it gets replaced. Do NOT commit the generated version; use `git diff` to confirm.
#
# Placeholders:
#   __GPU_HOST_IP__   — replace with GPU host static LAN IP (e.g., 192.168.1.100)
#   __GPU_HOST_NAME__ — replace with GPU host hostname (e.g., gpu-host)
#
# CRITICAL: The server cert SAN must include BOTH the IP and the DNS name.
#   If the orchestrator dials by IP, the IP SAN must match.
#   If the orchestrator dials by hostname, the DNS SAN must match.
#   A mismatch causes SSL handshake failure on every gRPC call (PITFALL 2).
#
# To regenerate with real values:
#   GPU_HOST_IP=192.168.1.100 GPU_HOST_NAME=gpu-host bash deploy/generate-certs.sh

subjectAltName=IP:__GPU_HOST_IP__,DNS:__GPU_HOST_NAME__
